Durban - Two men, aged 31 and 36, were sentenced to a total of 30 years imprisonment for a robbery committed in July 2017.
Slindelo Khoza and Sibusiso Nkala appeared in the Ladysmith Regional Court and were sentenced to 15 years imprisonment for robbery with aggravated circumstances, five years imprisonment for possession of firearm, five year imprisonment for attempted murder, three years imprisonment for housebreaking with intent to rob, two year imprisonment for discharging of a firearm likely to injure or endanger the safety of any person and six months imprisonment for possession of ammunition. They were also declared unfit to possess a firearm.

According to police spokesperson and Khoza and Nkala entered a business premises on Residency Road in Ladysmith and threatened an employee who was on duty. 
“He was instructed to lie on the floor while the two ripped a safe from the wall in an office. They took his cellphone and left whilst firing gunshots towards the victim. Police were contacted and they responded swiftly. They cornered the suspects in bushy area close to the scene of crime. A shootout ensued which resulted in the arrest of the two men who were taken into custody,” she said. 
Mbele said they were charged and appeared in court where the investigating officer successfully opposed bail while preparing the case docket for court proceedings.

“After several remands while in custody, the case was finalized and the accused were convicted,” Mbele said.